      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "i get that, but i've had bad lows in the past and it's really scary. i was just thinking if i don't have any carbs in my system, my body won't need that baseline insulin to stay stable. it seems like common sense that if you eat less, you need less insulin, right? i just want to avoid an emergency in the middle of the night.",
